<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tower</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-11"><hi rend="italic">February 11,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Tower reports that Department’s telegram, announcing that
                            instructions have been sent to the United States representatives at St.
                            Petersburg, Tokyo, and Peking, has been communicated to the German
                            minister for foreign affairs, and he replied that the necessary
                            instructions will be sent at once to the German representatives in those
                            capitals. He was also informed that the views of the United States will
                            be communicated immediately to all the neutral signatories of the
                            protocol of Peking.)</p>
                    </div>
